ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
0 = Tongue protrusion followed by mouth opening ; 1 = Mouth opening followed by tongue protrusion; 2 = Put in followed by take out; 3 = Take out followed by put in
0 = Objects mimicking human model (nonsocial stimulus); 1 = Human model (social stimulus)

ElementDescription: Raw Score of accuracy, sum of Adapted Legerstee Imitation Task
Mean rate per minute of mouth opening
Mean rate per minute of tongue protrusion
Mean rate per minute of both mouth opening and tongue protrusion
Mean rate per minute of put in followed by take out
Mean rate per minute of take out followed by put in
Mean rate per minute of both put in and take out
